<h1 class="Article-title">Browser &amp; Device Support</h1>
<p class="Text--lead">Below is a list of browsers/devices which Atomic must support has therefore been tested on.</p>

<hr>
<h2 id="section-support-grades"><a href="#section-support-grades" class="Text--resetLink">Grades of Support</a></h2>

<h3>Grade 'A' Support</h3>
<p>Grade ‘A’ browsers and devices support the highest level of functionality and visual richness and the user experience will be constant, though not necessarily identical. All code will be optimised for grade ‘A’ browsers and devices. This optimisation means that we will specifically check and debug the site’s presentation, functionality and behaviour.</p>

<h3>Grade 'B' Support</h3>
<p>Grade ‘B’ is the base level of support, providing core content and functionality. Delivered via semantic HTML and basic CSS the content and experience is highly accessible, may have limited (if any) decoration or advanced functionality. Layers of style and behaviour may be omitted.</p>

